@BT New Screen/briefs Text - no indent;From streetwalkers who charge as little as $5 (Bt161) per sex act to pimps who bring in tens of thousands a week, prostitution is big business in the United States a study released on Wednesday found.
The Urban Institute is the first research group to come up with a solid estimate on how much money changes hands and how the market for sex works in eight US cities.
In the tourism and convention hub of Atlanta, Georgia, the underground sex economy was pegged at $290 million a year, more than the illicit sale of drugs and guns combined.
Police described their struggles infiltrating brothels, massage parlours and topless bars that cater to specific ethnicities, Latino, Asian or Russian and Eastern European men, and are often run by organised crime rings. â€“ AFP
